    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "DNA barcoding and morphological analyses reveal a cryptic species of Miniopterus from India and Sri Lanka" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7859630>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7859628>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7859632>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7859644>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7859626> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7859630>
    dc:description "FIG. 3. Map of South and Southeast Asia showing sampling localities of M. phillipsi sp. nov. and Miniopterus specimens of mainland Asia mentioned in this study with biomes of ecoregions (Dinerstein et al., 2017). Type locality of M. phillipsi sp. nov. is marked by a black star" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7859630/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7859628>
    dc:description "FIG. 2. Plot of the first two components of a principal component (PC) analysis for craniodental measurements of the Miniopterus species in India and Sri Lanka (M. philipsii sp. nov. — blue circle; M. fuliginosus — green circle; M. magnater — black circle; M. pusillus — purple circle). Arrow points to holotype. See Table 2 for the variables used in this analysis and the loadings on PC1 and PC2" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7859628/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7859632>
    dc:description "FIG. 4. Portrait of M. phillipsi sp. nov. NMSL 2021.03.02.NH" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7859632/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7859644>
    dc:description "FIG. 8. Tragus of Miniopterus species in India and Sri Lanka. A — M. magnater (ZMMU S-172585); B — M. fuliginosus (ZMMU S-164505); C — M. phillipsi sp. nov. (NMSL 2021.03.01.NH, holotype); D — M. pusillus (ZMMU S-172595)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7859644/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7859626>
    dc:description "FIG. 1. Bayesian majority-rule consensus tree of the COI gene of Asian Miniopterus species. Dark circles depict nodes with Bayesian posterior probability ≥ 0.95 and maximum likelihood bootstrap support ≥ 70. The outgroup Chaerephon plicatus is not shown. Scale bar indicates the number of substitutions per site" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7859626/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

